divs: sighting detailssorry about this mix-up. i was looking at map quest south to north (right side up) when i should have been looking at it from north to south. so, the moon was setting to the west, not to the east as previously stated. the time was not 8:00pm, may 10. it was closer to 12:30am the 11th of may (i had forgotten that i had zeroed out the clock on the camera on a previous reboot). all other details are correct. the stars shown in the photos provided should give you an idea where the object was if you line up the stars with a star chart or star map. there are a few web sites that provide star maps. i try to provide the most accurate attention-to-detail in all my reports. i am sorry for the mix-up (no one is perfect). *(wit's first name deleted--cms\sg).
